  "$comment": "Obligations catalogue — PORTABLE DATA, no code (obligations.md:196 — no scoping, no mandate status, no page membership, no presentation on the record; all of those are computed elsewhere). 30 records: the 29 user-submitted fields of the mirrored car-insurance journey plus the system-handled `premium`. Each record: committed UUID `id` (the sole persistence key — frozen forever, stable across renames of `name`), unique meaningful `name` (the code/template/i18n binding string), open `type` (every type used must have a companion in the engine's type-companion registry), `cardinality` single|indexed with `indexedBy` {source, mutability} for indexed records, `constraints`, and bundled static option VALUE domains (option labels are presentation and live in flow.json). PROVISIONAL settlements carried by this file: (1) `indexedBy.controllingValue` is an invented schema extension realising FULF-18 pattern-2 — a derived obligation whose single fulfilment id IS the named controlling value, spawned/wiped by the orchestrator as the controller's answer includes/excludes it (open-for-human item 4); (2) `claimType` and `claimAmount` are two user-source indexed obligations sharing the fulfilment ids the orchestrator mints per added claim — one id per claim indexes both maps; (3) system-handled provenance is the scalar `handler` companion field on the record. Cross-references (controllingObligation) use UUID ids so renames never break them.",
